{
  "message": "Add fuzz targets for RESP/AOF/RDB parsers (frankenredis-0iyb)\n\nEstablishes fuzzing infrastructure with 4 targets for security-critical\nparser surfaces:\n\n- fuzz_resp_parser: RESP protocol crash detector with configurable limits\n- fuzz_resp_roundtrip: Round-trip invariant (parse(encode(frame)) == frame)\n- fuzz_aof_decoder: AOF file format crash detector\n- fuzz_rdb_decoder: RDB file format crash detector\n\nEach target has seed corpora with valid inputs covering:\n- Empty inputs\n- Minimal valid frames\n- Typical usage patterns\n- Edge cases (nested arrays, null values)\n\nRun with: cargo +nightly fuzz run <target>\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
